  {
    "id": "1747900000022",
    "channel_id": "19:chan-gocrft-help04@thread.tacv2",
    "team_id": "19:team-gocrft01@thread.tacv2",
    "from_user_id": "user-raj",
    "from_display_name": "Raj Patel",
    "content": "What's the idiomatic way to wrap errors so callers can still check the underlying one? fmt.Errorf with %w?",
    "content_type": "html",
    "importance": "normal",
    "created_date": "2026-01-05T12:53:05Z"
  },
  {
    "id": "1747900000023",
    "channel_id": "19:chan-gocrft-help04@thread.tacv2",
    "team_id": "19:team-gocrft01@thread.tacv2",
    "from_user_id": "user-tomas",
    "from_display_name": "Tomás Alvarez",
    "content": "Exactly, fmt.Errorf(\"loading config: %w\", err). Then errors.Is / errors.As at the call site. Don't %w if callers shouldn't depend on the inner type.",
    "content_type": "html",
    "importance": "normal",
    "created_date": "2026-01-05T13:04:03Z"
  },
  {
    "id": "1747900000024",
    "channel_id": "19:chan-gocrft-help04@thread.tacv2",
    "team_id": "19:team-gocrft01@thread.tacv2",
    "from_user_id": "user-jmurray",
    "from_display_name": "Jason Murray",
    "content": "Plus define sentinel errors with errors.New for the ones you want callers to match on. Keeps the public surface intentional.",
    "content_type": "html",
    "importance": "normal",
    "created_date": "2026-01-05T13:12:02Z"
  },
  {
    "id": "1747900000025",
    "channel_id": "19:chan-gocrft-gen01@thread.tacv2",
    "team_id": "19:team-gocrft01@thread.tacv2",
