    "created_date": "2026-03-14T05:55:13Z"
  },
  {
    "id": "1747900000034",
    "channel_id": "19:chan-gocrft-dsn03@thread.tacv2",
    "team_id": "19:team-gocrft01@thread.tacv2",
    "from_user_id": "user-leo",
    "from_display_name": "Leo Barros",
    "content": "Should a client library accept a context.Context on every method or store one on the struct? I always forget the consensus.",
    "content_type": "html",
    "importance": "normal",
    "created_date": "2026-03-21T08:47:04Z"
  },
  {
    "id": "1747900000035",
    "channel_id": "19:chan-gocrft-dsn03@thread.tacv2",
    "team_id": "19:team-gocrft01@thread.tacv2",
    "from_user_id": "user-jmurray",
    "from_display_name": "Jason Murray",
    "content": "Per-method ctx as the first arg. Storing a context on a struct is an anti-pattern, you lose per-call cancellation and deadlines.",
    "content_type": "html",
    "importance": "normal",
    "created_date": "2026-03-21T08:55:32Z"
  },
  {
    "id": "1747900000036",
    "channel_id": "19:chan-gocrft-dsn03@thread.tacv2",
    "team_id": "19:team-gocrft01@thread.tacv2",
    "from_user_id": "user-leo",
    "from_display_name": "Leo Barros",
    "content": "Right, that's the bit I keep second-guessing. Per-method it is. Thanks.",
    "content_type": "html",
    "importance": "normal",
    "created_date": "2026-03-21T09:01:31Z"
  },
  {
    "id": "1747900000037",
    "channel_id": "19:chan-gocrft-help04@thread.tacv2",
    "team_id": "19:team-gocrft01@thread.tacv2",
    "from_user_id": "user-evan",
    "from_display_name": "Evan Brooks",
    "content": "Best way to test code that calls time.Now()? My tests are flaky around DST boundaries.",
    "content_type": "html",
    "importance": "normal",
    "created_date": "2026-03-30T19:07:15Z"
  },
  {
    "id": "1747900000038",
    "channel_id": "19:chan-gocrft-help04@thread.tacv2",
    "team_id": "19:team-gocrft01@thread.tacv2",
    "from_user_id": "user-jmurray",
    "from_display_name": "Jason Murray",
    "content": "Inject a clock: a now func() time.Time field defaulting to time.Now. Tests pass a fixed clock. Makes DST and timeout tests deterministic.",
    "content_type": "html",
    "importance": "normal",
    "created_date": "2026-03-30T19:16:44Z"
  },
  {
    "id": "1747900000039",
    "channel_id": "19:chan-gocrft-help04@thread.tacv2",
    "team_id": "19:team-gocrft01@thread.tacv2",
    "from_user_id": "user-evan",
    "from_display_name": "Evan Brooks",
    "content": "Injecting the clock fixed the flakiness completely. Wish I'd done this months ago. Thanks!",
    "content_type": "html",
    "importance": "normal",
    "created_date": "2026-03-30T19:34:41Z"
  },
